Class CalculatorWSClient

java.lang.Object
  com.ttech.calc.logic.CalculatorWSClient

public class CalculatorWSClient
extends java.lang.Object

Logic class of the calculator application. CalculatorWSClient uses web services to handle caculator's requests and provides methods for performing calculations.

Method Detail

operate

public java.lang.Double operate()
The action handler when '=' (equate) button is activated. If there are no operations (e.g +, -, *, /) pressed before pressing '=' it takes no action, but if there is a waiting operation, operate() method performs the waiting operation and prepares calculator for a new operation.

Returns:
lvalue, the result of the operation performed.

operationPressed

public double operationPressed(int op)
Action handler when an operation (+, -, *, /) button is pressed. If there is a waiting operation before pressing this button, first the pending operation is completed, then the method changes calculator's state. After changing state of the calculator, it prepares calculator for a new input number.

Parameters:
op - {numeric value for an operation}
Returns:
lvalue, the number entered before pressing any of the operation buttons.

numberPressed

public double numberPressed(int num)
The action handler when an number (0-9) is pressed. According to the previously entered inputs and numbers, it updates the current value.

Parameters:
num -
Returns:
The value which is currently being edited. If there are no operation buttons pressed beforehand, lvalue will be returned, but if there is an operation pending, rvalue will be returned.

dotPressed

public double dotPressed()
If the dot button is pressed, the function changes the multiplier of the number that is currently being entered. However if the dot button is pressed before while entering the current input, it ignores the second dot button.

Returns:
The value which is currently being edited. If there are no operation buttons pressed beforehand, lvalue will be returned, but if there is an operation pending, rvalue will be returned.

resetD

public void resetD()
The method preparing the calculator for a new number input. Resets the location of the dot and the digit number that is currently being entered.

resetAll

public double resetAll()
Performs the action when "Clear" button is pressed. Resets the situation of the calculator to the initial point.

Returns:
lvalue, which is recently reseted to zero.
